node.text:
The way you start your day will determine your outcome. 

I used to dread the development phase of my business; all the hard work that needed to be put in 🚧🦺🧰🪚🔩⚙️🔧🔨🧱. Some times it would take me half the day to finally push myself to get started ⌛️. I eventually figured it out💡…You’ve got to make the start ☀️ of your day the hardest part, so everything else seems easy. If you find a way to challenge yourself outside of your business 🏋🏻🧘🏻‍♀️🏃🏻‍♂️🏃🏻‍♀️🏊‍♀️🚴‍♀️🧗‍♂️at the start of your day and you push yourself to your level of exhaustion🥵, watch how much easier the tasks in front of you are for the day. You will slice through them like butter. 🧈
🎥 Thanks to: @crossfitcrowntown

node.text:
Most people who are given an opportunity, dismiss it given the reason that they are too busy. People let their normal daily routine become the reason for their lack of success or their inability to really gain any traction in their lives. These people will always default to time as their number one excuse as to why they can’t get something started or finished. Don’t let that be your demise. Most successful people are extremely busy. They love being busy; in fact and it keeps them driven. Most people who are busy tend to get even busier because they want multiple opportunities to have income coming in. They realize that one plan always needs a backup plan and then the next plan leads to another. Being busy does not have to be a bad thing. It can be the one thing that separates you from most. The more time you put into something that can change your life, the more you can give to your future generation. Time is money. Make time. ⏰

node.text:
Leadership Development is an art 🖼. It’s an art that is commissioned of you and no one else . If you want to see leaders in your business or organization, you must lead from the front with massive action. Show them what to do by your very own example. That is the best way to teach anyone anything. Then, hold them accountable by challenging them to do the same. Developing leaders is no easy task. Don’t get discouraged when you don’t see your self being duplicated. It’s a process that takes time and it’s a process that has collateral damage of people leaving your organization. You will learn how to dial this process in over time and you will stop wasting your time on the needy and start investing your time in the deserving. Each leader will identify themselves to you through their actions, not their desperation. 💯

node.text: 1️⃣1️⃣Years flew by so quickly. What a story we have written so far. I am excited for the next chapters of our life. Our kids are growing so fast, it makes me sad. I love living my life with you and I couldn’t imagine it any other way. Thank you for being with me through it all. Here’s to the next 11. 🥂 Happy Anniversary @shannonbecerra . I love you. 😘

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by 𝐂𝐀𝐋𝐕𝐈𝐍 I 𝐁𝐮𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐞𝐬𝐬 𝐂𝐨𝐚𝐜𝐡 on August 14, 2021 tagging @kadenboross_. May be an image of 5 people, people standing, balloon and indoor.

node.text: Happy 1️⃣8️⃣ birthday to this kid right here @kadenboross_ . We are so proud of you and we are looking forward to the future for you. Thank you for being such a polite, respectful, hard working kid. Being a step dad is not an easy thing, but you make it easy for me. I appreciate that. I want you to know that I think of you as my own and I wouldn’t treat or think of you any differently. I’ve helped raise you since you were a little guy and I’ll always be here for you when you are a big guy. I hope that you can take the example I’ve given you and one day and possibly do that for someone else. I love you. Happy Birthday! Have some fun. You deserve it. 🥳
